  "buggy_functions": ["__rpc_execute"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "In net/sunrpc/sched.c, the __rpc_execute function (lines 783-792) unconditionally returns -ERESTARTSYS when a signal is caught during wait_on_bit, even if the underlying RPC task has already completed successfully. When an RPC response arrives from the server while the sync task is waiting on RPC_TASK_QUEUED bit and a signal arrives, the out_of_line_wait_on_bit call returns -ERESTARTSYS. The code then calls rpc_exit(task, -ERESTARTSYS), overwriting the successful RPC result. This causes NFS getattr to return error -512 even when the server replied successfully. The error propagates to nfs_revalidate_inode, which treats any non-zero error as failure, causing nfs_lookup_revalidate to mark the dentry invalid and zap caches, ultimately unmounting the autofs/NFS mount. The fix should check if the RPC task has already completed before overwriting the status with -ERESTARTSYS."
}

